Date of Birth: October 27, 1814<br/>
Birthplace: Trenton, New Jersey, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: January 4, 1857<br/>
Death: March 24, 1891<br/>
<br/>
Born Oct. 27, 1814, at Trenton, (now Barnveld) Oneida Co., New Jersey, to Daniel Wells and Catherine Chapin. Ordained apostle Jan. 4,1857; set apart as second counselor to President Young Jan. 4, 1857, at age 42; released at death of President Young Aug. 29, 1877; sustained as a counselor to the Twelve Apostles Oct. 6,1877; died March 24, 1891, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 76.